!When play begins or resumes
[when play|game begins|starts or resumes|continues]
This is the init script, it is executed before everything else. It is processed for a new game and for a loaded game.

!When play begins
[when play|game begins|starts]
Executed just before the game begins, but not after a game is loaded.

!When play resumes
[when play|game resumes|continues]
Executed just before the game resumes, but not after a new game is started.
 
!When play ends
[when play|game ends|finishes]
Executed when the game ends, usually after a [[end game]] statement.

